The Scene Is Set
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Several new and deadly breeds of virus have hatched themselves out 
inside your Amiga, and only you - as a computer controlled antidote 
capable of laying down "traps" for the viruses - can clean them up!
These nasties aren't the usual boot-sector annoyancies, they're the 
real thing - living demonspawn that'll eat away your circuit boards!

(Cabbage-brained humans please note the above paragraph is entirely
fiction for the sake of giving this addictive little number an excuse 
of a storyline. Thankyou.)


Loading The Game & How To Play It
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
VectorTrap requires 1-megabyte minimum, preferably a 1200 machine (for
maximum speed - I won't make up excuses around the fact that AMOS is 
not exactly the Nigel Mansell of programming languages, okay?) and you
will also save yourself some eye-strain if you've got a monitor 
because the mazes are tiny and very complex. You'll also need a 
joystick plugged into the usual port (no keyboard/mouse alternatives).

Once loaded, simply press FIRE to play. The tasty title screen and 
music will vanish and you'll find yourself slap-bang in the middle of 
the first level. 

The simple objective is to clear the Amiga's memory of nasty viruses 
(which flash on the scanner in the top left). You can only kill them 
by ensuring they collide with a set "trap", and these are laid down by
you when you press the fire button. You can only set a trap when you 
are completely still; the joystick must not be held in any direction, 
or you may end up teleporting instead (see below).

You begin with 20 traps, but you can pick up more in the maze. On the 
scanner, traps appear as yellow dots. There is no maximum to the 
amount you can carry. Your lives are indicated on the far right of the
screen and appear as red circles. After each level you complete, 
you'll get an extra life as a reward. There is also a score display, 
and an indication of how many viruses you have yet to kill. Sometimes 
the computer may catch on to your skill and insert another virus just 
to annoy you, but you need only kill as many as the display shows.

There are plenty of levels to go at, and several breeds of nasty 
virus. In the Amiga's memory maze you'll come across green slime; this
is acid formed by the viruses and must be AVOIDED at all costs!
                                          ~~~~~~~
By pressing FIRE and holding LEFT or RIGHT at the same time, you'll be
teleported to another position in the maze. The higher the level you 
are currently on, the bigger the maze will seem. However, the entire 
game is played within the SAME maze, so you might (might!) get to know
certain areas. Good luck on that one.


Hints And Tips
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
* If you're standing on a trap, you're safe until a virus collides 
  with you. After that, of course, you're vunerable again.

* Viruses home in on you very quickly and mimic your moves. By using 
  skillful manipulation, you can get them out into the open for 
  trapping without having to move any more than left and right a few
  times. Experiment and you'll see what I mean.

* You're never trapped yourself; teleporting is always an option, but 
  be careful, it's random so you could arrive in the middle of a nest 
  of viruses! 

* Keep stocked up on traps; if you run out, you're harmless and the 
  viruses will get you. Sometimes it's better to risk a teleport than 
  to try running for it.


